wdi2-NV.MNF.TXTL.ZS.UN.def: Value added in manufacturing is the sum of gross output less the value of intermediate inputs used in production for industries classified in ISIC major division D. Textiles and clothing correspond to ISIC divisions 17-19.
wdi2-NV.MNF.TXTL.ZS.UN.name: Textiles and clothing
wdi2-NV.MNF.TXTL.ZS.UN.source: United Nations Industrial Development Organization, International Yearbook of Industrial Statistics.
